[SN]TITLE[SN]
US stocks rebound after sharp falls

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
(Close): Wall Street shares rallied on Wednesday, recovering some of their losses from the previous trading session.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Dow Jones closed up 293 points, or 1.8%, at 16,351.
The Nasdaq jumped 114 points, or 2.5%, to 4,750 while the S&P 500 was up 35 points, or 1.8% at 1,949.
Earlier Chinese stock markets recovered from sharp falls, with analysts suggesting Beijing had intervened to prop up the market.
The Federal Reserve's Beige Book suggested steady economic growth for the US economy.
Technology firms led the day's gains, with Apple up 4.6%, Microsoft up 3.7% and Intel gaining 2.8%.
